104. 30. natura mundum administrari. Cicero might properly have omitted here the epithet sentiente, as he had already expounded the Stoic idea of nature, and the verb administrari itself indicates a designed, intelligent government. In what follows the epithet is sometimes ex· pressed‚ sometimes omitted.
